WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:05.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
In the day's other news:
Russia's official RIA
news agency reported
the U.S. and Russia

00:07.000 --> 00:10.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
are talking about creating a
cyber-security working group.

00:10.533 --> 00:15.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President Trump had raised a
similar idea during the G20
summit, but backed off under

00:15.233 --> 00:17.266 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
heavy criticism.

00:17.266 --> 00:21.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This latest report comes amid
multiple U.S. investigations
of Russian meddling in the

00:22.366 --> 00:24.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
2016 election.

00:24.333 --> 00:29.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Congressional Budget Office
says that a revised Senate
Republican health care bill

00:30.333 --> 00:33.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
leaves as many people uninsured
as a previous version.

00:33.766 --> 00:38.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The CBO reported today
that, under the bill,
another 22 million Americans
would lose coverage

00:39.933 --> 00:41.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
by 2026.

00:41.933 --> 00:46.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The measure would also reduce
federal deficits by $420
billion over the coming decade.

00:48.533 --> 00:53.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So far, GOP leaders still lack
the votes to debate the bill.

00:53.266 --> 00:58.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The health of Senator
John McCain dominated this
day at the U.S. Capitol.

00:58.066 --> 01:03.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The Arizona Republican has been
diagnosed with brain cancer,
and doctors removed a tumor,

01:04.266 --> 01:06.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
but McCain may need
additional treatment.

01:06.900 --> 01:11.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The news stunned lawmakers from
both parties, who said they're
hoping for the best for their

01:12.633 --> 01:13.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
longtime colleague.

01:13.233 --> 01:14.633 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

01:14.633 --> 01:15.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
PATRICK LEAHY (D), Vermont:
He's a good friend.

01:15.933 --> 01:18.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We agree and we disagree.

01:18.433 --> 01:23.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But he's one of the oldest
-- he keeps his word.

01:24.900 --> 01:27.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I know we will be praying
for him at mass this weekend.

01:27.800 --> 01:29.233 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
SEN.

01:29.233 --> 01:30.700 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
LINDSEY GRAHAM (R), South
Carolina: He may outlive us all.

01:30.700 --> 01:32.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I don't know what -- God only
knows how this thing ends.

01:32.833 --> 01:37.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I just ask God for one thing,
that he has a voice and he can
use it as long as possible.

01:39.833 --> 01:43.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: McCain is 80,
having survived seven years in
a North Vietnamese prison during

01:44.500 --> 01:46.466 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the Vietnam War.

01:46.466 --> 01:50.866 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was a Republican presidential
nominee in 2008 and is
serving his sixth term in the

01:51.433 --> 01:53.200 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Senate.

01:53.200 --> 01:56.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Today, he tweeted: "I
greatly appreciate the
outpouring of support.

01:56.433 --> 02:01.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Unfortunately, for my sparring
partners in Congress, I will
be back soon, so stand by."

02:03.366 --> 02:07.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the first time in the global
AIDS epidemic, more than half
of all those infected with

02:07.666 --> 02:10.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
HIV are on drugs
to treat the virus.

02:10.766 --> 02:15.766 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A United Nations report today
also finds that overall AIDS
deaths have fallen to about half

02:17.000 --> 02:18.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the level of 2005.

02:18.733 --> 02:23.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
The disease has killed
35 million people over
the past four decades.

02:25.400 --> 02:29.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
O.J. Simpson was granted
parole in Nevada today, after
nearly nine years in prison,

02:30.466 --> 02:32.566 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and could be freed in October.

02:32.566 --> 02:37.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The one-time pro football star
had been jailed for an armed
robbery in 2007 involving his

02:38.533 --> 02:40.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
own sports mementos.

02:40.566 --> 02:45.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Today, in a live-streamed
hearing, Simpson, now 70 years
old, pleaded his case to the

02:46.133 --> 02:47.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
state parole board.

02:47.300 --> 02:48.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
O.J.

02:48.600 --> 02:50.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SIMPSON, Inmate: I
have done my time.

02:50.633 --> 02:54.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, I have done it
as well and as respectfully
as I think anybody can.

02:54.200 --> 02:57.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think if you talk to the
wardens there, they will tell
you I have been -- I gave them

02:57.966 --> 02:58.966 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
my word.

02:58.966 --> 03:01.300 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I believe in the jury system.

03:01.300 --> 03:03.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I have honored their verdict.

03:03.600 --> 03:08.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Simpson's
defenders said that his 33-year
sentence was overly harsh, and

03:10.533 --> 03:14.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that he was really being
punished for the murders of his
ex-wife and her friend in 1994.

03:15.400 --> 03:17.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He was acquitted of
those killings in 1995.

03:17.833 --> 03:22.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The U.S. Senate today confirmed
a federal appeals judge,
despite a series of blog posts

03:24.366 --> 03:26.466 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that Democrats condemned.

03:26.466 --> 03:29.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Kentucky lawyer John
Bush was approved 51-47.

03:29.000 --> 03:34.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In one online posting, under a
pseudonym, he called abortion
and slavery -- quote -- "the

03:37.000 --> 03:39.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
two greatest tragedies
in our country."

03:39.333 --> 03:44.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He also linked to articles on a
far-right conspiracy Web site.

03:46.200 --> 03:49.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ExxonMobil was fined $2 million
today for violating U.S.
sanctions on Russia in 2014.

03:51.900 --> 03:55.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The oil giant said that it will
challenge the fine in court.

03:55.000 --> 04:00.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The U.S. Treasury Department
says the company showed reckless
disregard for sanctions by

04:01.566 --> 04:04.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
signing deals with
the head of Russia's
state-owned oil company.

04:04.666 --> 04:09.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
At the time, Secretary
of State Rex Tillerson
was ExxonMobil's CEO.

04:12.133 --> 04:15.100 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And on Wall Street, the
Dow Jones industrial
average lost about 29
points to close at 21611.

04:17.333 --> 04:21.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The Nasdaq rose about five, and
the S&amp;P 500 slipped a fraction.
